OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a dry day with
OL,6,Fpatchy cloud and plenty of bright and
OL,7,Fsunny spells breaking through. Mostly
OL,8,Flight winds but breezy near the coast.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FA dry evening with late sunny
OL,11,Fspells leading to clear spells after
OL,12,Fsunset. Overnight remaining dry with
OL,13,Flong clear spells for most, but
OL,14,Fturning cloudier in the west.
OL,15,
OL,16,CSaturday:FSunny spells to start inland
OL,17,Fbut soon turning cloudy through the
OL,18,Fmorning. Rain affecting coastal areas
OL,19,Fat first, then spreading eastwards
OL,20,Fthrough the afternoon and turning
OL,21,Fheavy at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
